    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="761"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d761">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2781: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-26T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>323. Department’s 312 via Paris.<note n="8" xml:id="d761fn8">See telegram no.
                        311, Oct. 13, to the Ambassador in France, with instructions to repeat to
                        London as no. 312, <ref target="#pg_920">p. 920</ref>.</note> French and
                    Japanese Governments have expressed concurrence in this Government’s proposal to
                        <pb facs="1044" n="924" xml:id="pg_924"/> wind up Interallied Committee and
                    Technical Board on October 31st. Please draw matter to attention of Foreign
                    Office and endeavor to expedite its reply.</p>
                <p>Referring to Department’s 209, July 17, 3 p.m.,<note n="10" xml:id="d761fn10">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_905">p. 905</ref>.</note>
                    inform Foreign Office and repeat to Paris as Department’s No. 339, that
                    Department has just been advised of Italian Government’s concurrence in
                    proposals outlined in original memorandum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
